headline: The Electric Car Transition Unravels Slowly, Then All at Once
summary: The European Commission backed away from what had been the world’s most aggressive timeline for phasing out internal-combustion engines, granting manufacturers and consumers more time to move off gasoline.  A day earlier, Ford Motor Co. announced $19.5 billion in charges tied to the retreat from an electric strategy it vowed to go all in on eight years ago.

headline: Cooper Standard Quick Connector with Integrated Temperature Sensor Named SPE® Automotive Innovation Award Finalist
summary: Cooper-Standard Holdings Inc. (NYSE: CPS) has been recognized as a 2025 Society of Plastics Engineers (SPE) Automotive Innovation Award finalist for its quick connector with integrated temperature sensor found on a General Motors electric vehicle. The innovation is recognized in the Chassis/Hardware category.
